{"repo": "virt-manager/virt-manager", "pull_number": 1003, "instance_id": "virt-manager__virt-manager-1003", "issue_numbers": [1002], "base_commit": "6fe47feca692ad8cff7b88fa4eb8bd328e0a9584", "patch": "diff --git a/virtManager/details/snapshots.py b/virtManager/details/snapshots.py\nindex 0d413a98dc..f2b229f5ed 100644\n--- a/virtManager/details/snapshots.py\n+++ b/virtManager/details/snapshots.py\n@@ -32,8 +32,8 @@\n def _make_screenshot_pixbuf(mime, sdata):\n     loader = GdkPixbuf.PixbufLoader.new_with_mime_type(mime)\n     loader.write(sdata)\n-    pixbuf = loader.get_pixbuf()\n     loader.close()\n+    pixbuf = loader.get_pixbuf()\n \n     maxsize = 450\n \n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Improper handling when `pixbuf` is `NoneType` leads to disabled snapshot UI\n\n**Describe the bug**\nWhat appears to be an issue in an upstream package (`gdk-pixbuf-2.44.4` ) triggers an improper handling state which renders snapshots unusable.\n\n**To Reproduce**\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\n1. Ensure `gdk-pixbuf-2.44.4` is installed\n2. Start `virt-manager`\n3. Navigate to a VM with snapshots\n4. Observe that you cannot see the details for nor can you take action on any of the snapshots.\n\n**Expected behavior**\nAfter a short code review, it looks like all the code is in place to handle an image not being loaded properly. However, a failure to check the `pixbuf` variable in `_make_screenshot_pixbuf()` of `virtManager/details/snapshots.py` causes the following unhandled error, which has a secondary effect of causing the snapshot interface to become unusable. The fix involves simply returning a `NoneType` from `_make_screenshot_pixbuf()` before the unhandled error can be triggered. Error is as follows:\n\n```\n[Fri, 31 Oct 2025 17:50:00 virt-manager 182496] ERROR (snapshots:853) 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'get_width'\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/main/projects/01-oss/virt-manager/virtManager/details/snapshots.py\", line 851, in _snapshot_selected\n    return\n  File \"/main/projects/01-oss/virt-manager/virtManager/details/snapshots.py\", line 658, in _set_snapshot_state\n    mode = _(\"External disk only\")\n    ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/main/projects/01-oss/virt-manager/virtManager/details/snapshots.py\", line 616, in _read_screenshot_file\n    mime = _mime_to_ext(os.path.splitext(filename)[1][1:], reverse=True)\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/main/projects/01-oss/virt-manager/virtManager/details/snapshots.py\", line 47, in _make_screenshot_pixbuf\n    factor = float(maxsize) / float(big)\n        ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nAttributeError: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'get_width'\n```\n\nAfter some debugging I was able to determine it was `pixbuf = loader.get_pixbuf()` that was the issue (https://github.com/virt-manager/virt-manager/blob/6fe47feca692ad8cff7b88fa4eb8bd328e0a9584/virtManager/details/snapshots.py#L35)\n\n**Screenshots**\n\n<img width=\"1131\" height=\"918\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f2c61ab4-5fe8-4f6f-9a49-bac729b5c000\" />\n\nAfter fix the error is handled gracefully (see PR in comments below).\n\n<img width=\"1139\" height=\"467\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d9a25fb4-4b32-4c91-8868-8901f69cf25b\" />\n\n**System (please complete the following information):**\n - Linux, Wayland, gtk3\n - virt-manager version: 5.1.0\n - libvirt version: 11.8.0\n\n**Additional context**\nSubmitting a PR with a fix. Tested with `meson test -C build` as suggested in CONTRIBUTING.\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "The issue was patched 2 months ago, but no release has been made. Is there a workaround for it in the meantime?\n@pauby The error does not appear if turn off the VM and create the snapshot.\nI am getting the same error when running on KDE Plasma\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/virt-manager/virt-manager/commit/108ae3ae5563904412c22394b109abc88a69bc39"], "created_at": "2025-10-31T21:57:50Z"}
{"repo": "virt-manager/virt-manager", "pull_number": 1029, "instance_id": "virt-manager__virt-manager-1029", "issue_numbers": [1023], "base_commit": "90e425b59a30f1dd4827de5cc480031d89391d3d", "patch": "diff --git a/virtinst/__init__.py b/virtinst/__init__.py\nindex 621acb238..eb874063a 100644\n--- a/virtinst/__init__.py\n+++ b/virtinst/__init__.py\n@@ -24,6 +24,7 @@ def _setup_i18n():\n \n     gettext.install(\"virt-manager\", BuildConfig.gettext_dir, names=[\"ngettext\"])\n     gettext.bindtextdomain(\"virt-manager\", BuildConfig.gettext_dir)\n+    locale.bindtextdomain(\"virt-manager\", BuildConfig.gettext_dir)\n \n \n def _set_libvirt_error_handler():\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "[flatpak] Locale partially applied\n- Distribution: _Fedora_ v. 43, _Silverblue_ edition (_OSTree_ model)\n- virt-manager v. 5.1.0\n- Distribution type: _flatpak_\n- Flatpak v. 1.16.1\n- libvirt version: [component missing from this application packaged as flatpak]\n\nHello. In the application the locale is partially applied when distributed in the _flatpak_ format while being fully applied when distributed in the _RPM_ format.\n\n```\n$ localectl | head -n 1\nSystem Locale: LANG=fi_FI.UTF-8\n$ flatpak config\nlanguages: *unset* (default: fi)\nextra-languages: *unset*\n```\n\n_note_: same output with the '`--user`' option.\n\n'`flatpak run org.virt_manager.virt-manager`'\n\n<img width=\"602\" height=\"639\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b8b37dc6-e3bf-4f0a-903a-64019d32d43a\" />\n\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/virt-manager/virt-manager/commit/20c181f256f3a15642b10390d8960a4c59b7e7ac"], "created_at": "2026-01-11T19:59:24Z"}
